\begin_layout Standard
The initialization round is to ensure that the imputation estimator 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{t}^{R}$
\end_inset

 is accurate enough to guarantee augmented estimation error bound.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Define 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
|\sum_{k=1}^{K}p_{t}(k)\sqrt{\rho_{t}}x_{k,t}^{\top}y|^{2}=|\sum_{k=1}^{K}p_{t}(k)\sqrt{\rho_{t}}r_{k,t}\Qb_{t}^{\top}y|^{2}\le\rho_{t}\sum_{k=1}^{K}p_{t}(k)(r_{k,t}\Qb_{t}^{\top}y)^{2}=\sum_{k=1}^{K}p_{t}(k)(\sqrt{\rho_{t}}x_{k,t}^{\top}y)^{2}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

